# Google Sheets Integration - Example .env.local
#
# IMPORTANT:
# 1. Create a file named ".env.local" in your project root (same level as package.json)
# 2. Copy the variables below and replace with your actual values
# 3. This file is in .gitignore, so it won't be committed to git
# 4. After adding/modifying this file, restart your dev server (Ctrl+C then 'pnpm dev')
#
# =====================================================================================

# Google Sheets API Configuration
# These are required for the user registration logging system to work

# Your Google Sheet ID (found in the sheet's URL)
# Example URL: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0j1k2l3m4n5o/edit
# Extract the ID: 1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0j1k2l3m4n5o
GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=1a2b3c4d5e6f7g8h9i0j1k2l3m4n5o

# Your Google API Key (from Google Cloud Console)
# Example: AIzaSyDxxx_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
GOOGLE_API_KEY=AIzaSyDxxx_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# =====================================================================================
# 
# HOW TO GET THESE VALUES:
#
# GOOGLE_SHEET_ID:
#   1. Open your Google Sheet
#   2. Look at URL: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/{ID}/edit
#   3. Copy the long string between /d/ and /edit
#   4. Paste it as GOOGLE_SHEET_ID value
#
# GOOGLE_API_KEY:
#   1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com
#   2. Select or create a project
#   3. Enable "Google Sheets API"
#   4. Go to Credentials page
#   5. Click "+ Create Credentials" → "API Key"
#   6. Copy the API key (starts with AIzaSy)
#   7. Paste it as GOOGLE_API_KEY value
#
# IMPORTANT SECURITY NOTES:
#   ⚠️ Never commit .env.local to git repository
#   ⚠️ Never share your API key publicly
#   ⚠️ Never post your keys in forums or issues
#   ⚠️ For production, use secure environment variables in your hosting platform
#
# =====================================================================================
